
[1]lachrymatory

   LACH'RYMATORY, n. A vessel found in sepulchers of the ancients, in
   which it has been supposed the tears of a deceased person's friends
   were collected and preserved with the ashes and urn. It was a small
   glass or bottle like a phial.
